<div id="content">
<h1 class="title">Deploying Alerts</h1>
<div id="table-of-contents">
<h2>Table of Contents</h2>
<div id="text-table-of-contents">
<ul>
<li><a href="#org06a3621">1. Create instance</a></li>
<li><a href="#org96f062a">2. Create and mount volume</a></li>
<li><a href="#org6aa96a3">3. Install docker and compose</a></li>
<li><a href="#orgbf41432">4. Download and Setup code</a></li>
<li><a href="#org1b6be26">5. Launching Alerts</a></li>
<li><a href="#org3024121">6. Monitoring Alerts</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org06a3621" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org06a3621"><span class="section-number-2">1</span> Create instance</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-1">
<p>
Follow the instruction on <a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/quickstarts/latest/vmlaunch/step-1-launch-instance.html">this</a> page to launch the instance.
<code>1. Choose an Amazon Machine Image</code> select an appropriate <code>Ubuntu</code> instance (preferable <code>16.04</code>). On
<code>2. Choose an Instance Type</code> select <code>C5.4x large</code>
Follow the rest of the steps as listed and launch the instance
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org96f062a" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org96f062a"><span class="section-number-2">2</span> Create and mount volume</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-2">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ebs-creating-volume.html">Create</a> a new <code>80GB</code> <a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/EBSVolumeTypes.html">general purpose SSD (gp2)</a> and <a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ebs-attaching-volume.html">attach</a> to the instance just created</li>
<li><a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ebs-using-volumes.html">format and mount</a> the volume</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org6aa96a3" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org6aa96a3"><span class="section-number-2">3</span> Install docker and compose</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-3">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Install <a href="https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/">docker</a> and <a href="https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/">docker-compose</a></li>
<li>Modify the configs to store all docker data in <code>/data</code> directory. Follow <a href="http://forums.docker.com/t/how-do-i-change-the-docker-image-installation-directory/1169">this</a> guide.</li>
<li>Start the docker engine with the following command <code>sudo service start docker</code></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgbf41432" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgbf41432"><span class="section-number-2">4</span> Download and Setup code</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-4">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Cd into <code>/code</code> and create a new folder for the code <code>cd /data &amp;&amp; mkdir Alerts</code></li>
<li>Clone the latest code from github master branch</li>
<li>Create a new <code>.env</code> file in the <code>/data/Alerts</code> folder and setup environment variables. These may vary, depending upon the code. <b>Make sure there is no whitespace between names and values</b>. Here is an example <code>.env</code> file.</li>
</ul>

<div id="org6162157" class="figure">
<p><img src="./img/env-file.png" alt="env-file.png" />
</p>
<p><span class="figure-number">Figure 1: </span>An example <code>.env</code> file</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org1b6be26" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org1b6be26"><span class="section-number-2">5</span> Launching Alerts</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-5">
<p>
<code>sudo docker-compose up -d</code> would start all the containers in the background. Remove <code>-d</code> flag for code to run in the same window
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org3024121" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org3024121"><span class="section-number-2">6</span> Monitoring Alerts</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-6">
<p>
<code>sudo docker-compose logs -ft --tail=&lt;num-of-lines&gt;</code> to view the logs of the running instances in realtime
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
